CONFIGURATION

To configure with default options the library, type

  $ make config

Several options can be added to the configure script, they include:

   - cc=[compiler]     The C compiler used in cmake tests, default: gcc
   - cxx=[compiler]    The C++ compiler to use, default: g++
   - prefix=[path]     Installation path, default: /usr/local
   - shared=[bool]     Build a shared library, default: true
   - assert=[bool]     Enable the assert macro, default: true
   - doc=[bool]        Configure to build the documentation, default: true
   - build=[string]    Build types: Debug, Release, RelWithDebInfo, MinSizeRel,
                       default: None


